  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mexico Earthquake Trauma Relief &amp; Youth Training</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ten days of extensive Youth Leadership Training will train 80 youngsters, who have already gone under second stage Trauma Relief program from Earthquake affected communities, to become leaders, and will continue working with the earthquake victims in their area, teaching them tools and skills to overcome trauma, anxiety, stress, intense fear, helplessness, relationship breakdown, reduce violence and strengthen the community links. 20 teams of these leaders will benefit 3,000 people per year.</narrative>
  </description>
